<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd7b92c9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s5586"><num value="5586">§ 5586.</num><heading> Interim authority of the Secretary</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="iddd7b92ca-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s5586/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to perform the functions of the Bureau under this part until the Director of the Bureau is confirmed by the Senate in accordance with <ref href="/us/usc/t12/s5491">section 5491 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="iddd7b92cb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s5586/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Interim administrative services by the Department of the Treasury</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Department of the Treasury may provide administrative services necessary to support the Bureau before the designated transfer date.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="iddd7b92cc-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/203/tX/s1066">Pub. L. 111–203, title X, § 1066</ref>, <date date="2010-07-21">July 21, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2055">124 Stat. 2055</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
